  "texts": [
    "However, applying these methods to general instruction following remains challenging due to the lack of automatic success criteria, motivating our exploration of rubric-based rewards to bridge the gap between human preferences and verifiable signals.",
    "Rubric-based RL.",
    "Our work is closely related to previous and concurrent work that also explores the use of rubrics in reinforcement learning.",
    "For example, Bai et al. (2022b) propose Constitutional AI, which uses a set of principles to guide model behavior through self-improvement without direct human feedback.",
    "More recently, Zhou et al. (2025); Viswanathan et al. (2025) show that checklists or rubrics can be used to generate responses for Direct Preference Optimization (DPO; Rafailov et al., 2023) or Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO; Guo et al., 2025) and achieve better alignment."
  ],
